http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/TSRTC-to-operate-3605-bus-services-to-Medaram/article13995069.ece

The Telangana State Road Transport Corporation (TSRTC) has decided to operate 3,605 bus services to the biennial Sammakka-Sarakka Jatara, to be held from February 17 to 19 in Medaram of Warangal district.Minister for Transport P. Mahender visited the RTC bus station complex and held a review meeting with officials over the arrangements for the jatara.Talking to newsmen, he said that they would operate special bus services to the biennial jatara from 51 places from all 10 districts of the State. The district administration will erect temporary bus stand at Medaram on the sprawling 50 acres of land, besides providing amenities for pilgrims such as - toilets, drinking water, sheds, queue lines etc at a cost of Rs. 1.92 crore.